==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|mistaken}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{term|mistaka||lang=non|to take in error, to miscarry}}, equivalent to {{prefix|mis|take|lang=en}}. Cognate with Icelandic {{m|is|mistaka||to mistake}}, Swedish {{m|sv|misstaga||to mistake}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/mɪˈsteɪk/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-mistake.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪk|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[error]]; a [[blunder]].
#* '''1877''', Henry Heth, quoting [[w:Robert E. Lee|Robert E. Lee]], in "Causes of the Defeat of Gen. Lee's Army at the Battle of GettysburgOpinions of Leading Confederate Soldiers.", ''Southern Historical Society Papers'' (1877), editor Rev. J. WM. Jones [http://books.google.com/books?id=iDIFAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA292&dq=lee+%22mistakes+were+made%22&hl=en&ei=fchaTbu4L8L98AaVs4n-DQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=lee%20%22mistakes%20were%20made%22&f=false]
#*: After it is all over, as stupid a fellow as I am can see that '''mistakes''' were made. I notice, however, that my '''mistakes''' are never told me until it is too late.
# {{context|baseball|lang=en}} A pitch which was intended to be pitched in a hard to hit location, but instead ends up in an easy to hit place

